value: Common in the northwestern Indian Ocean (Arabian Sea). Breeding grounds undiscovered, but probably on the coast of southern Arabia. Ranges at sea in the Indian Ocean to lat. 5° S. One record in the Pacific: Lisianski, Leeward Hawaiian Chain. Another record, of 3 birds, in the Adriatic Sea: imported birds?
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Vagrant: Gulf of Aden, off Somalia, Seychelles. (Note that breeding grounds are unknown.)

subcat_descr: Bill length (sex unknown) - Nares to tip
